This week's Carlos cartoon weighs up the value of the vote in itself – as the basic unit of democracy – against the arguably greater value of activist citizenship in defence of true democracy. From Russia to Turkey to Egypt to the US, flawed or unfree elections are legitimising autocrats. To avoid that fate, South Africans must keep a constant, critical eye on the daily workings of the state. You might be interested in:
